# UB Workload Coding Standards

## File boundaries

- `authorized_users.gs` is the single source of truth for authorization data and helpers. Do not redefine `isUserAuthorized`, `getUserRole`, `getUserName`, or `getFacultyUnderUser` in other files.
- `workload.gs` owns all Firebase access, workload record CRUD, summaries, approvals, profiles, and reporting.
- `index.html` owns all DOM manipulation and UX; it calls backend functions only via `google.script.run`.

## Backend patterns (Apps Script)

- Wrap all external calls (`UrlFetchApp.fetch`) in `try/catch`, log with `console.error`, and return `{ success, message, ... }` objects.
- Always resolve the current user with `Session.getActiveUser().getEmail()` and enforce role checks before returning or mutating sensitive data.
- Use the `safeEmail = email.replace(/\./g, ',')` and `recordId = \`\${safeEmail}_\${semester}\`` conventions consistently.
- When adding new reporting or summary functions, ensure each faculty member is counted at most once per logical aggregation.

## Frontend patterns (`index.html`)

- Use Bootstrap classes and the existing UB color CSS variables (`--ub-purple`, `--ub-gold`) for visual consistency.
- Add new workload entry types by following the existing `addWorkloadEntry` / `updateSubcategories` / `updateActivities` pattern.
- Run client-side validation before submissions and show clear, user-friendly error messages.
- Use `google.script.run.withSuccessHandler(...).withFailureHandler(...)` for all backend calls, and do not assume network success.

## Auth & roles

- When implementing new flows, check `getUserRole` and restrict operations appropriately:
  - Chairs/Deans/Super Admin may see and act on multiple users’ data.
  - Faculty should only see and edit their own submissions.
- Update `AUTHORIZED_USERS.deans`, `AUTHORIZED_USERS.chairs`, `facultyMap`, and `deanFacultyMap` together when roles or structures change.
